Lance Futch met with President Obama at Hill Air Force Base in Utah on Friday to discuss jobs for veterans in the field of solar energy . 
  The National Guardsman was told it was an 'informal meeting' with a White House official to discuss veterans jobs . 
  He sat at a table with Obama, Senator Orrin Hatch and Salt Lake City Mayor Ralph Becker . 
  Futch said he thought he was going to talk about how to help veterans get more jobs in the solar energy field . 
 